          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "When I heard about Vidya Vana and the teachers who’ve come together and opened it, I had no doubt in my mind that this is where I want my child to go.\nI wanted a homely environment for my child where I know she’s going to not to learn what every play school teaches but also things that are so essential for their upbringing in today’s world, a more empathetic and down to earth human being. Everyday when I drop Anahat to school I always know that she’s with her masis who love her like their own. As the first place of learning, I couldn’t have chosen a better school than Vidya Vana. So thankful each day to all the teachers to have opened this beautiful place.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Vidya Vana - Sector 26A"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Karishma Baijal"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-06-12",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Vidya Vana is an exceptional place for young children to learn and thrive. The school's infrastructure is well-planned, modern, and child-friendly. Every detail has been carefully considered to create an inspiring and comfortable environment for young learners.\n\nWhat sets Vidya Vana apart is the quality of its faculty. The team of experienced and highly trained teachers go above and beyond to create a nurturing and stimulating learning experience for their students. Their love of teaching and passion for early childhood education is evident in the way they interact with the children.\n\nThe curriculum is meticulously designed to cater to the developmental needs of young children. The school offers a mix of structured and unstructured learning activities that keep the children engaged and excited to learn. Through play and exploration, the children develop their creativity, critical thinking skills, and social-emotional abilities.\n\nOverall, I am incredibly impressed by Vidya Vana. It is evident that every aspect of the school is thoughtfully planned and executed with the students' wellbeing and learning in mind. I highly recommend this school to anyone in search of a quality early childhood education for their child.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
